JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South African retail sales rose by 1.5% year-on-year in April, beating market expectations, after increasing 0.9% in March, data from the statistics office showed on Wednesday.Analysts polled by Reuters had forecast a 0.6% year-on-year increase in retail sales in April.On a month-on-month basis, sales inched up by 0.3% and were also up 0.3% in the three months to April compared with the same period last year, Statistics South Africa said. 